==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rosaniline
<hw>Ros*an"i*line</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Rose</ets> + <ets>aniline</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A complex nitrogenous base, <chform>C20H21N3O</chform>, obtained by
oxidizing a mixture of aniline and toluidine, as a colorless crystalline
substance which forms red salts. These salts are essential components of
many of the socalled aniline dyes, as <xex>fuchsine</xex>, <xex>aniline
red</xex>, etc. By extension, any one of the series of substances
derived from, or related to, rosaniline proper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rosarian</ent>⟦br⟧
